Description:
The Workiz journey began in sunny San Diego, California, with a group of locksmith pros who spent their days surfing and their nights rescuing people locked out of their homes. As their locksmith business grew, they quickly realized how much time was being wasted on repetitive, mundane tasks. Frustrated by the lack of software tailored to their needs, they decided to build their own field service digital headquarters.

In 2015, Workiz was born. Fast forward to today, Workiz has become the #1 field service management platform, trusted by over 120,000 service professionals. We are also proud to be the leading FSM in AI, helping field service businesses of all sizes streamline operations, boost efficiency, and drive revenue growth.

Workiz is built by field service pros, for field service pros, with the goal of turning top service professionals into thriving business professionals. With tools designed to simplify every aspect of your operations—from calls and scheduling to dispatching, invoicing, and reporting—Workiz empowers you to focus on growing your business and achieving your dreams.

Our mission is simple: to help your business thrive today so that when you’re ready to retire, you’ll have the freedom to choose your next steps with confidence and success.

At Credit Repair Cloud we’re reimagining the world of credit repair. This means being bold in our decisions and creating software experiences that revolutionize the industry--all while keeping our core values in mind. 

We are a talented global team that leads with heart, passion and optimism. A team that welcomes different ideas, talents, and cultures.

 At Credit Repair Cloud, we create SaaS software that allows Credit Heroes to help their clients with credit troubles, change lives, and make a great living in the process .

First started in 2012, we have become the leader in the credit repair industry, and our customers have helped thousands of clients clean and improve their credit . Through the use of our platform, we’ve helped our customers change almost 12 million lives.

Today we’re a stable, fast-growing (5X Inc. 5,000) company with numerous team members around the globe and products that our industry loves. 

Learn more at  www.creditrepaircloud.com

Description:
SmartSuite is an AI-native work platform that connects the workflows that run your business. Think of SmartSuite as a Work Operating System (Work OS)—a unified foundation for data, automation, AI, permissions, integrations, and reporting that helps teams build, manage, and scale work across the organization.

Most teams start with a single workflow—then expand as they see the power of connected work across departments. SmartSuite makes it easy to standardize processes, assign clear ownership, automate follow-through, and gain real-time visibility from leadership dashboards down to the details in every record.

SmartSuite includes purpose-built solution suites across four core areas:

• Governance, Risk, Compliance & Resilience — unify risk, compliance, audit, third-party risk, operational resilience, business continuity, regulatory readiness, privacy, AI governance, and ESG.
• IT Service Management (ITSM) — manage incidents, changes, requests, assets, and service operations, with direct connections to evidence, issues, and remediation.
• Project & Portfolio Management — align teams on priorities, track execution across initiatives, and report progress against goals and OKRs in real time.
• Business Operations — run processes across sales, marketing, product, operations, HR, finance, procurement, and more.

With a modern UI and enterprise-grade governance, SmartSuite helps organizations replace spreadsheets and fragmented point tools with connected workflows, accountable execution, and measurable outcomes.

Description:
Merge is the leading provider of customer-facing integrations and agent tools for frontier LLMs, Fortune 500 organizations, and B2B SaaS companies. 

Our platform offers two core products: Merge Unified, which enables businesses to add hundreds of integrations to their products with a single API, and Merge Agent Handler, which empowers AI agents with secure access to thousands of third-party tools. 

Merge's enterprise-grade platform handles the entire integration lifecycle, from authentication and security to monitoring and maintenance. 

Thousands of companies trust Merge to accelerate product development, unblock sales, reduce customer churn, and save engineering resources—allowing them to focus on their core product.

Merge is backed by $75 million in funding from Accel, NEA, and Addition. Merge was founded in 2020 by Shensi Ding and Gil Feig and is proudly built in San Francisco, New York City, and Berlin.

Merge is on Linkedin's 2025 Top Startups list (see here: https://hubs.li/Q03NHPnb0), and we're hiring! 

Apply here: https://www.merge.dev/careers

The hila platform helps enterprises minimize the risks of AI, while taking full advantage of the transformation potential of reliable AI systems.

Description:
Tonkean is the first-of-its-kind process orchestration platform. Powered by AI, Tonkean helps enterprise internal service teams like procurement and legal create process experiences that people actually follow. 

Maximize adoption, efficiency, and compliance. Intelligently orchestrate the intake, triage, and resolution of every request. 

With a library of preconfigured process templates and a 100% no-code workflow editor, Tonkean is the automation platform of choice for many innovative F500 companies. With full governance controls, enterprises can guarantee compliance while maximizing adoption—all without any change management and no code. Founded in 2015, Tonkean is headquartered in Palo Alto with R&D in Tel Aviv.

Description:
MindK is a software development and IT consulting company that helps businesses build software products, automate business processes, modernize technology and infrastructure. Our company was founded in Ukraine but has grown into a multi-cultured team with employees across Central and Eastern Europe for the last few years. We also opened branch offices in the Czech Republic and the USA (California). 
We use modern technology and accumulated experience in project delivery to help you with technology-transformation initiatives.

What our team can do for you:
- Software engineering: we develop new products, extend/modernize existing functionality or infrastructure, build third-party integrations, etc.
- Team augmentation: we provide highly skilled engineers to augment your in-house capabilities.
- IT consulting: we access your business challenges and help you transform your operations using technology.

Among the industries we excel in are:
- Education
- Recruitment and HR
- Construction and Property Management
- Financial Services
- Advertising technology

Contact us and challenge our team with your idea: https://www.mindk.com/contacts/  

Or get to know us better: https://www.mindk.com/company/

Description:
haku is the all-in-one platform for both endurance events and nonprofit fundraising. Our clients use haku to manage everything from registrations, donations, events, memberships, DIY and P2P fundraising, e-commerce, event ticketing, marketing, memberships, loyalty, reporting and supporter engagement in one intuitive solution.

haku connects every participant and supporter interaction in a single source of truth. Teams unlock powerful data, smart automations, and real-time insights that drive revenue, increase efficiency, and create more meaningful relationships with participants and donors.
Flexible configuration and enterprise-grade security let haku adapt to your workflows, not the other way around. With transparent pricing and full access to platform features, more of every dollar goes directly to your mission.

Trusted by leading organizations such as the Bank of America Chicago Marathon, Leukemia Research Foundation, New York Road Runners, Colon Cancer Coalition, Marine Corps Marathon, Mercy Home, Houston Marathon, Zoo Miami, Mercedes-Benz Corporate Run, Dress for Success, Blistering Pace,  and many more.

Learn more at www.hakuapp.com
